  - conditional optimism
  - knowledge architecture
  - agent augmentation
  - RAG
  - benchmark
  - council synthesis
  - multi-model deliberation

abstract: >-
  The Abundance Codex is an open-source narrative dataset of 273 entries across
  21 Grand Challenge domains, designed to shift AI agent reasoning from
  scarcity-default to evidence-anchored abundance. The corpus comprises 252
  base entries co-authored by four frontier models (Claude Opus 4.6, ChatGPT
  5.4 Thinking, Gemini 3.1 Pro, Super Grok) under human curation, plus 21
  council_synthesis entries produced through multi-model deliberation. Evaluated
  via the ACE benchmark (504 matched-pair judgments, single Opus 4.6 judge),
  augmented models show +0.38/5 improvement in reasoning quality, with
  cost-efficient models showing 3-4x larger gains than frontier models.
